<BaseLayout title="About Sterling Prentice" description="Sterling Prentice is an analyst at Swiss Finance Investment Bank covering equity capital markets and M&A across London, Zurich, New York, and Stockholm.">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">About the Author</h1>
    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <p>Sterling Prentice is an analyst at Swiss Finance Investment Bank covering equity capital markets and M&A across London, Zurich, New York, and Stockholm. He writes for college and MBA candidates targeting investment banking roles. Prior coverage includes IPO bookbuilding on the Glacier Point transaction (Solaris Tek A.S., BIST) under MD Mira Zhang and ECM Head Julian Brant.</p>

      <h2>About Investment Banker</h2>
      <p>Investment Banker is the editorial arm of Swiss Finance Institute, built to give aspiring bankers the information that actually matters - not recycled career-coach advice or watered-down interview prep. Every article is written from the perspective of someone who works on live deals and sits in the chair.</p>
      <p>The content spans five verticals: Technical (modeling and valuation), Interview Prep (questions and strategies), Job Search (networking and recruiting), Industry (bank culture and compensation), and Recruiting Insider (life after the offer). Each piece is designed to be the single best resource on its topic.</p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>For editorial inquiries or corrections, reach out at <a href="mailto:contact@swissfinanceinstitute.ai">contact@swissfinanceinstitute.ai</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
